nd finished second to last in their block, failing to advance to the semifinals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.njpw.co.jp/match/detail_result.php?e=794|title=World Tag League 2013|accessdate=2013-12-07|work=[[New Japan Pro-Wrestling]]|language=Japanese}}</ref> Following a disappointing fan reaction to a confrontation between Okada and Naito, NJPW announced that fans would get to vote whether they or Shinsuke Nakamura and Hiroshi Tanahashi for the IWGP Intercontinental Championship would be the true main event of the Tokyo Dome show.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.njpw.co.jp/news/detail.php?nid=10590|script-title=ja:\u3010WK8\u3011\u30aa\u30ab\u30c0\u3068\u5185\u85e4\u3001\u4e2d\u9091\u3068\u68da\u6a4b\u3001\u30c7\u30f4\u30a3\u30c3\u30c8\u3068\u98ef\u4f0f\u304c\u3001\u30bf\u30a4\u30c8\u30eb\u30de\u30c3\u30c1\u306b\u5411\u3051\u3066\u30b3\u30e1\u30f3\u30c8\uff01\u30101\u30fb4\u6771\u4eac\u30c9\u30fc\u30e0\u5bfe\u6226\u30ab\u30fc\u30c9\u767a\u8868\u8a18\u8005\u4f1a\u898b\u3011|date=2013-11-11|accessdate=2013-12-09|work=[[New Japan Pro-Wrestling]]|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.f4wonline.com/more/more-top-stories/102-japan/33934-new-japan-announces-fan-voting-for-tokyo-dome-main-event|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131111153624/http://www.f4wonline.com/more/more-top-stories/102-japan/33934-new-japan-announces-fan-voting-for-tokyo-dome-main-event|title=New Japan announces fan voting for Tokyo Dome main event|last=Meltzer|first=Dave|authorlink=Dave Meltzer|archivedate=2013-11-11|date=2013-11-11|accessdate=2013-12-09|work=[[Wrestling Observer Newsletter]]}}</ref> When the results were released on December 9, Okada and Naito had gotten only half the votes Nakamura and Tanahashi had gotten and, as a result, lost their main event spot for NJPW's biggest show of the year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.njpw.co.jp/news/detail.php?nid=10739|script-title=ja:\u3010WK8\u30111.4\u6771\u4eac\u30c9\u30fc\u30e0\u5168\u30ab\u30fc\u30c9!! \u3000\u30e1\u30