ssdate=2013-10-14|work=[[New Japan Pro-Wrestling]]|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wrestleview.com/misc-news/44319-10-14-njpw-ippv-results-tokyo-japan-tanahashi-okada|title=10/14 NJPW iPPV Results: Tokyo, Japan (Tanahashi/Okada)|last=Namako|first=Jason|date=2013-10-14|accessdate=2013-10-14|work=Wrestleview}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tokyo-sports.co.jp/prores/mens_prores/197970/|script-title=ja:\u68da\u6a4b\u304c\u30b2\u30fc\u30e0\u3056\u3093\u307e\u3044\u306e\u81ea\u5815\u843d\u751f\u6d3b|date=2013-10-27|accessdate=2015-12-08|work=[[Tokyo Sports]]|language=Japanese}}</ref> With the win, NJPW claimed that Okada had taken over Tanahashi's spot as the \"[[Glossary of professional wrestling terms#ace|ace]]\" of the promotion.<ref name=KingofProWrestling2013/> On November 9 at [[Power Struggle (2013)|Power Struggle]], Okada defeated Karl Anderson in a rematch of the 2012 G1 Climax finals for his sixth successful title defense.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.njpw.co.jp/match/detail_result.php?e=772|title=Power Struggle|accessdate=2013-11-09|work=[[New Japan Pro-Wrestling]]|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://live.sportsnavi.yahoo.co.jp/live/fight/all/2013110901/|script-title=ja:\u65b0\u65e5\u672c\u30d7\u30ed\u30ec\u30b9\u300cPower Struggle\u300d|date=2013-11-09|accessdate=2013-11-09|work=Sports Navi|publisher=[[Yahoo!]]|language=Japanese|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131109153400/http://live.sportsnavi.yahoo.co.jp/live/fight/all/2013110901/|archivedate=2013-11-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wrestleview.com/misc-news/44882-11-9-njpw-ippv-results-osaka-japan-okada-anderson|title=11/9 NJPW iPPV Results: Osaka, Japan (Okada/Anderson)|last=Namako|first=Jason|date=2013-11-11|accessdate=2013-11-11|work=Wrestleview}}</ref> Okada and his next challenger, 2013 G1 Climax winner Tetsuya Naito, faced off on November 23 during the first day of the [[2013 World Tag League]] in a match, where Okada and Yoshi-Hashi were victorious over Naito and [[La Sombra (wrestler)|La Sombra]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.njpw.co.jp/match/detail_result.php?e=782|title=World Tag League 2013|accessdate=2013-12-07|work=[[New Japan Pro-Wrestling]]|language=Japanese}}</ref> Okada and Yoshi-Hashi however managed to win only one of their five remaining matches in the tournament and finished second to last in their block, failing to advance to the semifinals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.njpw.co.jp/match/detail_result.php?e=794|title=World Tag League 2013|accessdate=2013-12-07|work=[[New Japan Pro-Wrestling]]|language=Japanese}}</ref> Following a disappointing fan reaction to a confrontation between Okada and Naito, NJPW announced that fans would get to vote whether they or Shinsuke Nakamura and Hiroshi Tanahashi for the IWGP Intercontinental Championship would be the true main event of the Tokyo Dome show.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.njpw.co.jp/news/detail.php?nid=10590|script-title=ja:\u3010WK8\u3011\u30aa\u30ab\u30c0\u3068\u5185\u85e4\u3001\u4e2d\u9091\u3068\u68da\u6a4b\u3001\u30c7\u30f4\u30a3\u30c3\u30c8\u3068\u98ef\u4f0f\u304c\u3001\u30bf\u30a4\u30c8\u30eb\u30de\u30c3\u30c1\u306b\u5411\u3051\u3066\u30b3\u30e1\u30f3\u30c8\uff01\u30101\u30fb4\u6771\u4eac\u30c9\u30fc\u30e0\u5bfe\u6226\u30ab\u30fc\u30c9\u767a\u8868\u8a18\u8005\u4f1a\u898b\u3011|date=2013-11-11|accessdate=2013-12-09|work=[[New Japan Pro-Wrestling]]|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.f4wonline.com/more/more-top-stories/102-japan/33934-new-japan-announces-fan-voting-for-tokyo-dome-main-event|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131111153624/http://www.f4wonline.com/more/more-top-stories/102-japan/33934-new-japan-announces-fan-voting-for-tokyo-dome-main-event|title=New Japan announces fan voting for Tokyo Dome main event|last=Meltzer|first=Dave|authorlink=Dave Meltzer|archivedate=2013-11-11|date=2013-11-11|accessdate=2013-12-09|work=[[Wrestling Observer Newsletter]]}}</ref> When the results were released on December 9, Okada and Naito had gotten only half the votes Nakamura and Tanahashi had gotten and, as a result, lost their main event spot for NJPW's biggest show of the year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.njpw.co.jp/news/detail.php?nid=10739|script-title=ja:\u3010WK8\u30111.4\u6771\u4eac\u30c9\u30fc\u30e0\u5168\u30ab\u30fc\u30c9!! \u3000\u30e1\u30a4\u30f3\u306f\u4e2d\u9091vs\u68da\u6a4b\u306b\u6c7a\u5b9a!! \u5f8c\u85e4vs\u67f4\u7530! \u771f\u58c1vs\u30d5\u30a1\u30ec! \u5c0f\u5cf6\u304cNWA\u6311\u6226! \u30cf\u30fc\u30ea\u30fc\u30fb\u30ec\u30a4\u30b9\u6c0f\u3082\u767b\u5834!! \u3000\u201cX\u201d\u3068\u306f\uff1f|date=2013-12-09|accessdate=2013-12-09|work=[[New Japan Pro-Wrestling]]|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.f4wonline.com/more/more-top-stories/102-japan/34366-tokyo-dome-main-event-is|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131212083933/http://www.f4wonline.com/more/more-top-stories/102-japan/34366-tokyo-dome-main-event-is|title=Tokyo Dome main event is|last=Meltzer|first=Dave|authorlink=Dave Meltzer|archivedate=2013-12-12|date=2013-12-09|accessdate=2013-12-09|work=[[Wrestling Observer Newsletter]]}}</ref> That same day, Okada became the first wrestler in 25 years to win back-to-back MVP awards from ''Tokyo Sports''.<ref name=TokyoSports2013MVP>{{cite web|url=http://www.tokyo-sports.co.jp/prores/mens_prores/212526/|script-title=ja:\u30aa\u30ab\u30c0\u30fb\u30ab\u30ba\u30c1\u30ab\u304c\uff12\u5e74\u9023\u7d9a\u300c\u30d7\u30ed\u30ec\u30b9\u5927\u8cde\u300d\uff2d\uff36\uff30\uff01\uff12\uff15\u5e74\u3076\u308a\u306e\u5feb\u6319|date=2013-12-10|accessdate=2013-12-09|work=[[Tokyo Sports]]|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://battle-news.com/news/2013/12/002053.php|script-title=ja:\u30aa\u30ab\u30c0\u304c2\u5e74\u9023\u7d9a\u3067\u30d7\u30ed\u30ec\u30b9\u5927\u8cdeMVP\u3092\u53d7\u8cde\uff01\u53f2\u4e0a4\u4eba\u76ee\u306e\u5feb\u6319\u3060\u304c\u3001\u672c\u4eba\u306f\u300c\u5f53\u305f\u308a\u524d\u306e\u7d50\u